{=# Render the raw experiment catalogue only when it adds information beyond the laws:
     when several experiments were grouped into each law (experiments > laws). At 1:1 the
     per-experiment hypotheses merely restate the law statements already in Results, so the
     appendix is omitted to avoid duplication. #=}
{% if ctx.experiments and (not ctx.laws or ctx.experiments|length > ctx.laws|length) %}
## Experiment catalogue {#sec-experiments}

The {{ ctx.experiments|length }} AutoDiscovery experiments grouped into the {{ ctx.laws|length }} candidate laws. Each law's reproduction verdict is in [Results: empirical laws](#sec-laws).

{=# Show the execution-status column only when it varies; when every experiment shares the
     same status (typically all "success") it is noise, so the id↔hypothesis pair is enough. #=}
{% set statuses = ctx.experiments|map(attribute='status')|select|unique|list %}
{% if statuses|length > 1 %}
| Experiment | Status | Hypothesis |
|--------|--------|----------------------------------------------|
{% for e in ctx.experiments %}| {% if e.link and clickable %}[{{ e.experiment_id }}]({{ e.link }}){% else %}{{ e.experiment_id|md }}{% endif %} | {{ e.status|md }} | {{ e.hypothesis|mathify|md }} |
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
| Experiment | Hypothesis |
|--------|--------------------------------------------------------|
{% for e in ctx.experiments %}| {% if e.link and clickable %}[{{ e.experiment_id }}]({{ e.link }}){% else %}{{ e.experiment_id|md }}{% endif %} | {{ e.hypothesis|mathify|md }} |
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
